http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/title.value: Health K-4 Content Standards with Benchmarks and Performance Standards

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: The New Mexico content standards with benchmarks and performance standards for health education are mandated for students in grades K-12.  (The New Mexico content standards with benchmarks for health education were adopted in March 1997 as part of 6 NMAC 3.2; the benchmarks and performance standards were revised in June 2007.)  Effective June 30, 2009.
Students will comprehend concepts related to health promotion and disease prevention. Students will:
identify/describe/understand the relationships between personal health behaviors and individual well-being:

describe how personal choices relate to health and how the consequences of those choices affect self and others (e.g., smoking, lack of physical activity, nutrition, personal hygiene, personal safety);
describe characteristics of healthy and unhealthy relationships (e.g., describe the unique differences of self and others); and
describe what is meant by good personal hygiene (e.g., describe the importance of hand washing in disease prevention).

identify characteristics of healthy and unhealthy relationships (e.g., describe the unique differences of self and others); and
recognize what is meant by good personal hygiene (e.g., describe the importance of hand washing in disease prevention).

identify and understand how personal choices relate to health and how the consequences of those choices affect self and others (e.g., smoking, lack of physical activity, nutrition, personal hygiene, abstinence, personal safety);
identify and describe characteristics of healthy and unhealthy relationships (e.g., describe the unique differences of self and others);
discuss what is meant by good personal hygiene (e.g., describe the importance of hand washing in disease prevention); and
list the steps associated with refusal skills and their relationship to the decision-making process.

list positive health choices and activities that promote health and help prevent diseases.
